Package modalLogic.tableau

Interface Summary
Heuristics<P> Provides interface of replacable heuristics used by tableau algorithm.
Rules<P> Provides interface to exchangeable expansion rules.

Branch<P> The currently investigated branch of the tableau.
DefaultHeuristics<P>  
DisjunctSelector<P> Provides methods to select disjuncts.
DynamicBacktracking<P> Performs dynamic backtracking when clash occurs on current branch.
ExpandedDisjunctions<P> A list of expanded disjunctions.
KRules<P> Expansion rules for modal logic K (contains propositional logic).
LabelledFormula<P> Container for subformulas together with world labels and meta information.
LabelledFormulas<P> Manager of all labelled formulas.
PreBlocked<P> Manage blocked formulas before execution of tableau.
Tableau<P> Implementation of the tableau algorithm.
UnitPropagation<P> Implementation of unit propagation to predict the best expansion due to current branch.
World<P> A world in the sense of modal logic (i.e.
WorldRelation<P> Models a reachability relation between two worlds (see Kripke Models)
Worlds<P> Management of all created world in the tableau.
